# PPTX skill

When asked to create or edit a .pptx file (or to use the "PowerPoint skill"):

1. **Read** `skills/pptx/SKILL.md` and, for HTML-to-PPTX workflows, `skills/pptx/html2pptx.md` in full.
2. **Use** the workflows and scripts under `skills/pptx/`:
   - **New deck from HTML:** Create one HTML file per slide (body 720pt × 405pt for 16:9); all text in `<p>`, `<h1>`–`<h6>`, `<ul>`/`<ol>`, or `<span>`; no manual bullets; no CSS gradients (rasterize to PNG first). Run a Node script that uses `skills/pptx/scripts/html2pptx.js` and PptxGenJS.
   - **Edit existing .pptx:** Unpack with `python skills/pptx/ooxml/scripts/unpack.py`, edit XML, validate, pack with `skills/pptx/ooxml/scripts/pack.py`.
   - **Template-based:** Follow the template workflow in SKILL.md (thumbnail, inventory, rearrange, replace).
3. **PptxGenJS colors:** Use hex without `#` (e.g. `"FF0000"`).
4. **Design:** State content-informed design choices; use web-safe fonts; ensure contrast and readability.

Source: [anthropics/skills/pptx](https://github.com/anthropics/skills/tree/main/skills/pptx).
